[h1]Torchlight ★★★★★☆☆☆☆☆ [5/10][/h1]  
[b]Intro[/b]
It's a fun RPG/Hack and slash/Dungeon Crawler game, the game looks good and is well optimized though it lacks fullscreen borderless (you can use a 3rd party program though).

It's quite limited without installing some mods, didn't pay much attention to the story tbh. Some of the achievements are very grindy like fishing 1k fish? Oh and buggy, had completed my Very Hard run and didn't get any difficulty completion achievements.

[b]PROS:[/b]
+ Game looks good;
+ Interface and skill tree is very beginner friendly;
+ Replayability, there's an endless dungeon where you keep going down floors and fight tougher monsters/getting better loot;
+ Mod support;
+ A friendly companion (dog or cat) which can help you on battles and carry loot/go to town to sell stuff while you keep on going;
+ 3 different classes with various build customizations and each of these can be built differently;
+ Good optimization/performance;
+ Hardcore mode.

[b]CONS:[/b]
- Story is meh average;
- Quest rewards are terrible;
- Getting low level loot when you're higher leveled, sometimes under leveled unique items only good for 2nd characters/runs;
- On higher difficulties even with a lot of defense there's stuff that might insta kill you, making flat health one of the most important stats in hardcore;
- When you're enchanting an item there's a chance it might disenchant it completely rendering it useless which isn't fun at all;
- Some achievements are not fun at all ex: 1k fish;
- Some achievements don't trigger, such as complete the game on Very Hard didn't grant me the achievement;
- No skill respecialization;
- No fullscreen borderless support;
- No buff/debuf tooltip;
- Not that much of room to stash items;
- You can't split a stack of items.

[b]FINAL VERDICT[/b]

Do note that most of these cons can be fixed with mods. Ultimately the game is fun to play and worth completing it, as any other game grab it on a sale.

[b]Mods[/b] that I use:

* Very Healthy Pet;
* Enchant Never Wipe;
* Merchant Pack;
* Smarter Pets & Minions;
* Spellborder;
* Torchlight II pets;
* Shaped Gems Complete;
* More Stash;
* Additional Gem Availability;
* Respect Mod;
* Stacking Mods;
* Better Balanced Sale Prices;
* Better Quest Rewards;
* Artic Wolf.
